ygData.subject: Re: [EQ_women] I'm playing again
ygData.msgSnippet: ... I played my ranger on Tholuxe a long time and I think she s still in Legends.  There were a LOT of teenagers in the guild as it was growing. Just wondering
ygData.messageBody:
On Fri, 12 Jan 2001, Judy Tyrer wrote:

> Hi sister! Boy does that sound familiar. Which guild?
I played my ranger on Tholuxe a long time and I think she's still in
Legends. There were a LOT of teenagers in the guild as it was growing.
Just wondering if it's the same group.

Hey hon =) The guild I'm in is called Rebirth.

> My new char will be a Barb Shaman on Tunare. I'll be playing with a
40 wiz and 16 necro. I love flexible characters and was always laughed at
for being a tanking druid. I remember my Shaman friends being able to do
crowd control when there was no enchanter. Tanking all the time. Apparently
the only time Shaman really is boring and kinda sucks is when you're doing
buffing circles and they have to spend hours and hours buffing people.
Plus, they get alchemy which sounds REALLy fun!

I hope you have fun with your shaman!

>
> Welcome back! And I know just how you feel about Brell. Some great
friends, but some very awful server politics.

Yeah =(

Christina
